The paper discusses a web-based toolbox for crowdsourcing visual attention, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also mentions using annotation tools and image processing techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper discusses analyzing the data using natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
